  "calendarNotes": "Virginia Beach City Public Schools (VBCPS) opens the 2026–2027 school year on August 24, 2026, following staff workdays from August 14–21. Unlike most Virginia districts, VBCPS organizes its academic year into four quarters rather than semesters — quarter-end dates fall on October 30, January 22, April 8, and June 11, and typically include early-release dismissal used for parent conferences or professional development. Labor Day extends to a four-day weekend: both Friday, September 4 and Monday, September 7 are school holidays. Veterans Day (November 11) is observed as a full school holiday, consistent with Virginia Beach's large active-duty military population. Thanksgiving Break runs November 25–27; Winter Break runs December 21 through January 1, with classes resuming January 4. Spring Break is scheduled March 29–April 2, 2027 — coinciding with peak resort season on the Virginia Beach oceanfront, when traffic and hotel rates near Atlantic Avenue are significantly elevated. The school year ends for all students on June 11, 2027.",
